menu "DESPOT Board Selection"

choice DESPOT_BOARD
    prompt "Target hardware board"
    default DESPOT_BOARD_CROWPANEL_ADV_9
    help
        Selects the physical board / display panel the firmware is built for.
        Only meaningful on ESP32-P4 builds; the legacy ESP32-S3 RGB path is
        selected by the IDF target and ignores this choice.

    config DESPOT_BOARD_CROWPANEL_ADV_9
        bool "CrowPanel Advanced 9inch ESP32-P4 HMI (1024x600 IPS touch, WiFi6)"
        help
            Elecrow CrowPanel Advanced 9-inch ESP32-P4 HMI AI display,
            1024x600 IPS with capacitive touch and an ESP32-C6 WiFi-6
            co-processor. This is the primary / default target board.

            EK79007 MIPI-DSI panel (no CH422G IO-expander); GT911 touch on
            I2C SDA45/SCL46 (RST40, INT42); backlight PWM on GPIO31
            (active-high); DSI PHY LDO channel 3, panel rail LDO channel 4.
            16MB flash, 32MB PSRAM (ESP32-P4NRW32).

    config DESPOT_BOARD_WAVESHARE_P4_7
        bool "Waveshare ESP32-P4-WIFI6-Touch-LCD-7B (1024x600, EK79007, CH422G)"
        help
            Secondary board. Waveshare 7-inch MIPI-DSI panel (EK79007 driver
            IC) with a CH422G I2C IO-expander driving DISP/backlight/touch-
            reset. Backlight on GPIO32 (active-low), panel reset on GPIO33,
            DSI PHY LDO channel 3. 32MB flash.

            To build for this board, apply the Waveshare overlay:
            idf.py -DSDKCONFIG_DEFAULTS="sdkconfig.defaults;sdkconfig.defaults.esp32p4;sdkconfig.defaults.waveshare_p4_7" build
endchoice

endmenu
